# Styling and design tokens

This project does **not** use Tailwind. Prefer **design tokens**, **CSS Modules**, and **`pageTypography`** helpers so UI stays consistent and CMS-driven pages match the rest of the site.

## Tokens (source of truth)

- Edit JSON under **`tokens/`** (e.g. `tokens/color.json`, `tokens/font.json`).
- Run **`npm run tokens:build`** (also runs automatically before **`npm run build`** and **`npm run build-storybook`** via `prebuild` / `prebuild-storybook`).
- [Style Dictionary](https://amzn.github.io/style-dictionary/) outputs **`src/styles/generated/tokens.css`** (`:root` CSS variables). **Do not hand-edit** the generated file; change JSON and rebuild.

## Wiring

- **`src/app/globals.css`** imports generated tokens first, then defines base typography, links, layout helpers (e.g. skip links, `.prose`, `.sr-only`), and small global utilities.
- Use **`var(--color-…)`** and other token variables in CSS modules or globals.

## Components and pages

- Colocate **`ComponentName.module.css`** with the component or route; import as `styles` and use `className={styles.foo}`.
- **`src/lib/pageTypography.ts`** re-exports classes from **`src/styles/pageTypography.module.css`** for shared shell/banner/body copy on CMS pages. Use these for tool/project pages and long-form layouts when appropriate.
- Storybook stories may use small **`*.stories.module.css`** files for layout-only wrappers.

## Reference

- Storybook → **Foundations → Design Tokens** (`src/stories/DesignTokens.stories.tsx`, `src/stories/designTokens.data.ts`).
- **`README.md`** → Customization → Styling for the same workflow in prose.

## CMS-driven tool pages

When adding routes like `/runs`, `/pileated-watch`, etc., follow **`.cursor/rules/cms-driven-tool-pages.mdc`** for copy and data, and apply **tokens + modules** here for layout and type—not utility-class frameworks.
